The code copies from response->data_iov as a read-only source (memcpy destination = connection->rp.resp_iov.iov, source = response->data_iov). If response->data_iov is declared as a non-const pointer (e.g. MHD_iovec_ *data_iov) but is only used for reading, it should be declared const (e.g. const MHD_iovec_ *data_iov). Therefore this usage indicates a violation of MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 unless response->data_iov is already declared const.
